Package org.propelgraph

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ClearableGraph
    This interface exists to provide a generic interface for a method to quickly clear out the vertices and edges of a graph without deleting the graph.
    CollaborativeFilterSupport
    This interface allows one to declare support for various collaborative filtering methods.
    CSVFileLoadingGraph
    This interface is generally for classes that have methods that are particularly fast at loading CSV files.
    DeleteableGraphFactory
    Implementations of this interface and the LocatableGraphFactory interface work together to delete graphs objects.
    GraphExternalVertexIdSupport
    This interface is designed to allow calling code to find a vertex based on the value that was specified when the Vertex was created.
    LocatableGraph
    This interface is used by Graph classes that support a LocatableGraphFactory.
    LocatableGraphDirectory
    Implementations of this interface and the LocatableGraph interface work together to help persist and rehydrate graph objects.
    LocatableGraphDirectoryRecord
    This interface works in conjuction with the LocatableGraphDirectory interface to provide a way for callers to get a list of graphs in a given directory and present a user interface describing the directory.
    LocatableGraphFactory
    Implementations of this interface and the LocatableGraph interface work together to help persist and rehydrate graph objects.
    OptionalMethodVerifier
    This interface allows the caller to check if the implementation of a generic interface has really implemented a method of that interface.
    RDFHTTPLoadingGraph
    This interface is generally for classes that have methods that are particularly fast at loading RDF from HTTP streams.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LocatableGraphFactoryFactoryImpl
    This class implements most of the glue needed to implement the LocatableGraphFactory support.
    LocatableGraphStub
    This is an empty class that can be used as a place holder of a graph that might be too expensive to instatiate until one is certain it is needed.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AlreadyExistsException
    Exception that indicates that something already exists.
    NotFoundException
    Exception that indicates that something was not found.
    UnsupportedFActionException
    Exception that the passed faction parameter is not supported or not supported for this graph url.
    UnsupportedMethodException
    Exception that indicates that the object does not support the specified method.
